"Manhunter" (1986), directed by Michael Mann. 120 minutes. Rated R. A stylish, 
intensely suspenseful psycho-thriller (from the director of "Miami Vice " and 
"Crime Story") about a cop tracking a bizarre serial killer by discovering the 
killer instinct within himself. With "Crime Story's" Dennis Farina and Stephen 
Lang. KELLY McPHILLIPS 
